t is why I consider an uncluttered night sky a Have you ever been out in the desert away from local lights and most people The sky is dark and The Milky Way is ablaze with more detail than you thought The beauty and wonder takes your breath Now imagine you live in the worst ghetto say in Due to light pollution you have never seen a dark You might in fact never not in your whole life ever see the majesty of the night Every where around you you see squalor and through your life runs a thread of What is there to live for I admit these two scenarios are extreme examples but I have seen I for one need dreams and hopes and yes beauty as a reason for That is why I consider an uncluttered night sky a George George Krumins The Serpent and the Rainbow Pufferfish Observatory o